: "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "We do add .gitattributes configurations for cases where we do want to keep files (dot or not) under git.\r\n\r\nRecently while adding 10TB of shub into annex which I intentionally created without `-c text2git`, thus assuming that everything would go into annex, I saw it reporting that `.shub-log (non-large file; adding content to git repository)` and some of which where quite damn large (so I ended up with 600MB .git/objects).\r\n\r\nSo I wondered if it wouldn't be less of cognitive load on users if we just treat any general .dotfile as a large file (unless `-c text2git` and alike)?", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5582/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5582/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}